{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, interpretability remains a concern in industrial and regulatory contexts, where decision-makers may prefer transparent mechanisms over black-box outputs.",
    "As such, hybrid strategies that combine AI with traditional methods are gaining traction.",
    "For example, AI can be used for pre-screening or real-time monitoring, while final validation is conducted through chemical assays or expert panels.",
    "This layered approach ensures both efficiency and reliability, bridging the gap between innovation and standardization.",
    "While common challenges in olfaction and gustation highlight cultural variability, interpretability, and data privacy, systemic limitations within current AI research frameworks remain under-addressed."
  ]
}